*** WELCOME ***Twin Kingdom Valley surroundsthe lake of Watersmeet. It isbelieved that the lake itselfhas some mystical properties.It is also said that thewise may look upon the Secretof Life which lies near by.Two Kings reside in the valleyand are sworn enemies.--- PRESS ANY KEY ---PLAYING THE GAMEAs with all creatures whoinhabit the valley, you havea certain strength, which willdecrease, if you are attacked.Normally your strength willgradually recover, but thereare exceptions to this rule.Beware of creatures who roamthe valley, some are friendly& some are not.--- PRESS ANY KEY ---OBJECT OF THE GAMEThe game has many tasks tocomplete, and one ultimategoal. Which in time youwill discover.The treasures you collectalong the way can be safelystored in the cabin, whichyou rent from the keeperof the Sword Inn.--- PRESS ANY KEY ---COMMANDSFor a complete command listtype "HELP" in the game.The game accepts input like:"HIT GUARD WITH AXE","ENTER CABIN", "NORTH","N","GIVE THE ELF THE SWORD" or"GET LAMP". Study the list ofcommands carefully, each oneis there for a reason.--- PRESS ANY KEY ---COMMANDS"INVENTORY" will list theitems in your possession.The game has many picturesof locations & objects withinthe valley, some of these holduseful clues. Use "VIEW" toexamine your objects.Type "SCORE" to check yourprogress within the game.--- PRESS ANY KEY ---COMMAND INPUTThere are Predictive & Tapinput modes, set in theOption Menu. Predictive willwork out the word you wantto type by the keys you press.i.e. for GUARD type 48(GU).Tap allows input of eachletter to build the word. Bothmethods work in the same wayas SMS texting on the phone.--- PRESS ANY KEY ---KEYS2 - 9 = A to Z entry# = Space* = Display picture0, Joystick centre = EnterTop Left = EnterTop Right = Menu or Delete--- PRESS ANY KEY ---LOAD & SAVEThe game has load & Savefeatures from the Menu.It also has an auto savefeature, which will createa resume file if you end thegame accidentally by pressingthe red end call key.Resume will restart the gamefrom where you left off.*** HAPPY WANDERING ***